-- Peru Stocks: Candente, Casa Grande, Rio Alto, Southern
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-04-16T21:47:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/peru-stocks-buenaventura-candente-rio-alto-southern.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the close of trading.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for a second day, dropping 0.3
percent to 23,268.50. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  slid 0.2
percent to 2,959.83.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner, fell
2.5 percent to $4.35 after gold declined for a second day in  New
York .  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, dropped 2 percent to 2.90 soles after tin fell to a
three-month low in  London .  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peru’s biggest copper
producer, slid 1.1 percent to $30.70 after copper slumped to a
three-month low in London, said  Jorge Ramirez , a trader at Lima-
based brokerage Coril SAB.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian copper
exploration company, fell 1 percent to 99 cents.  Casa Grande (CASAGRC1)  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, fell 2.6 percent to 17 soles after
sugar dropped to a 10-month low in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
